text.section:
The rules in addition to other matters shall specifically provide for and cover the following:
Physical, mental, educational, citizenship, and age requirements for new officers;
Physical, mental, educational, citizenship, age, and length of service requirements for promotion from lower to higher rank or classification;
A requirement that police officers have five (5) years of service as police officers before being eligible for promotion to the rank of sergeant;
Provision for open, competitive, written, oral, and other mental and physical examinations to determine the relative fitness of all candidates for original appointment and for promotion;
A requirement of public notice of all examinations to be given by the merit board;
Organization and meetings of the board; and
Procedure and conduct of public hearings.
